<br>
There would be, so far as I can see, one minor application of this, in that you could pull a single through a group of spawns that did not come to the aid of the single, but would have previously aggroed onto the pet.  However, this can only occur when both spawns are close, as <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet attack</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> has a fairly short range.<br>
<br>
Thank you for your ideas, and I look forward to more.  I hope that this simple but radical change would solve most major <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> concerns, without resorting to other means to increase <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Magician Damage Output</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
Just let use what we have already been given.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
