Pets need to be fixed, it's what your class does, and your summons need to be upgraded, but your nukes are where they should be, or a little less.  You should nuke more that druids, I will give you that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>(Title left blank)</span><br>  Posts: 4398<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/7/02 11:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pets</span><hr size=1> Verant said (possibly covering sloppy ass coding but this was their official line) that the pet pathing and lack of control was to balance out their power.  Pets have since this point had their power lowered (especially post-50 pets relative to their level).<br>
<br>
As such, the pathing problems, by default, should be reduced or eliminated as they aren't required as a balance issue any more.  Giving someone an atomic bomb as part of their design then making it unusable in many areas is just crappy from the start anyway.<br>
<br>
Making pets indifferent would be a good option, although simply making them obey better, path better, and be controllable from any distance would be a good option as well.<br>
<br>
Basically I think most people can agree that Magicians nuke well enough, perhaps too well before level 50.  Making their pets more effective without being more powerful (and putting more, better summons in the game, replacing the crappy ones with useful ones etc) would be all very good for the class which is all but extinct these days.<br>
<br>
Post 50 the nukes are just sad, but it appears Verant's approach to post 50 is to have nukes a very minor part of the game (til 60) and encourage multiple pulls. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usilverbladetheenchanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silverblade the Enchanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/8/02 3:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pets</span><hr size=1> Magicians aren't a damage dealing class?!<br>
